comments: Truly an awful experience. An exceptionally large amount of work was given out. The work was not returned with comments in a. timely manner on anything but the response papers. She was a very difficult professor to deal with and if you demonstrated true knowledge of her subject she seemed to take it personally.

comments: This class was decent at best. Lynette is knowledgeable but her teaching style is very scattered. The three hour lecture was used very inefficiently. Class discussions were the best part but the information from those was hardly usable on tests. It would be a much better class if it was better structured.
